An if-else statement is used to execute a certain code block if a certain condition is true, or execute another code block if the condition is false. It is used to control the flow of the program.

Example: 

let x = 10;

if (x > 5) {
  console.log("x is greater than 5");
} else {
  console.log("x is not greater than 5");
}

